**Analysis:** Villain is loose-passive (VPIP ~45%, PFR ~5%) and rarely 3-bets (0 three-bets in 20 hands). No stored patterns exist yet beyond the summary. With **TT** in the SB, this is a premium hand against a wide, passive caller — I should raise for value, as villain will frequently call and rarely re-raise.

A raise to **7** (3.5× the BB) is a standard value raise that builds the pot while staying exploitably profitable vs. a station.

